    <div class="title">
      Synthesis - The CSIT Magazine</div>
    <div class="content">“Synthesis” is a semester magazine by the Chemical Society of IISER Thiruvananthapuram, 
      aiming to bridge the gap between the chemical fraternity and society, and providing a platform for students
       to express their thoughts on scientifically relevant topics. The magazine embraces interdisciplinary research,
        featuring diverse genres of writing that span various scientific forums, not just limited to chemistry. 
        It seeks to produce fresh content, foster chemical awareness, and combine different ideas into a synergistic
         and relevant product for readers.

      <br><br>
      The magazine’s name, “Synthesis”, reflects its mission. 
      It underscores the belief that solutions to global problems 
      lie in novel synthesis, making the magazine and the research 
      it covers perennially relevant. The name embodies the passion 
      for the subject and the relevance of the knowledge it seeks to 
      disseminate. The team behind “Synthesis” is dedicated to ensuring 
      that the magazine grows and continues to captivate its readership.
    </div>
      
  
  </div>
