    <div class="cover"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1AOAXn1CK_RUx-0aWh6DKIM20tg-GZklY/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank"><img src="{{ get_asset synthesis1.jpg }}"></a></div>
    <div class="text"><div class="title">About the Cover:</div><div class="content"> 
      In this issue, delve into the intricate world of chemical reactions with a comprehensive review on SN2 and SN2’ 
      mechanisms. Explore the fascinating realm of molecular glues and their applications, and unravel the mysteries of aromaticity 
      in organic compounds. ‘Cosmic Cookery’ takes you on an interstellar journey to discover the chemical processes that cook up the
       universe. The Hof-Zeff rule is demystified, providing a deeper understanding of chemical behavior.
       <br><br>

Moreover, we celebrate the Nobel Prize in Chemistry 2022, discussing the groundbreaking work that earned this prestigious 
accolade. Additionally, don’t miss the interview summary with Dr. Soumen De, who sheds light on the exciting developments 
in dynamic supramolecular chemistry.
 <br><br>
