        <div class="text"><div class="title">About the Cover:</div><div class="content">
           In this edition, we spotlight a potential Haber-Bosch killer, an innovative approach that could revolutionize 
           nitrogen fixation, potentially replacing the century-old process that has been the backbone of agricultural 
           fertilizers. We also delve into unusual structural crises, where the stability of chemical structures is challenged,
            leading to unexpected and exciting findings.
            <br><br>

          Our journey through chemistry takes us back in time as we explore chemistry in the ancient world,
           uncovering the roots of alchemy and early medicinal practices. In contrast, we bring you the latest research 
           in India, highlighting the country’s contributions to the global chemical sciences community.
